Class Card

java.lang.Object

  • Constructor Details

    • Card

      public Card(String type, String number, String cardholder, String cvv, String pin, boolean isTapEnabled, boolean hasChip)
      Create a card instance.
      Parameters:
      type - The type of the card.
      number - The number of the card. This has to be a string of digits.
      cardholder - The name of the cardholder.
      cvv - The card verification value (CVV), a 3- or 4-digit value often on the back of the card. This can be null.
      pin - The personal identification number (PIN) for access to the card. This can be null if the card has no chip.
      isTapEnabled - Whether this card is capable of being tapped.
      hasChip - Whether this card has a chip.
      Throws:
      SimulationException - If type, number, or cardholder is null.
      SimulationException - If hasChip is true but pin is null.
